1
00:01:11,989 --> 00:01:14,909
Take it. It belonged to your father.

2
00:01:20,206 --> 00:01:21,207
[camera beeps]

3
00:01:25,753 --> 00:01:30,174
[Sergei, in Russian] The man who killed
your father gave you that gun.

4
00:01:32,176 --> 00:01:33,469
Min Ju-yeong!

5
00:01:33,552 --> 00:01:35,012
Skell-choilz.

6
00:01:38,516 --> 00:01:40,017
[in English] Why did you do it?

7
00:01:41,727 --> 00:01:43,103
Why did you do it?

8
00:01:49,443 --> 00:01:50,694
Answer me!

9
00:01:51,237 --> 00:01:52,613
Answer!

10
00:02:03,958 --> 00:02:05,417
[thud]

11
00:02:08,587 --> 00:02:11,382
[Ju-yeong panting]

12
00:02:16,470 --> 00:02:19,390
[chuckles, pants]

13
00:02:51,255 --> 00:02:52,256
[gunshot]

14
00:03:17,781 --> 00:03:18,908
[gasps]

15
00:03:20,618 --> 00:03:22,036
[grunting]

16
00:03:26,582 --> 00:03:28,500
[Ju-yeong] You did this.

17
00:03:29,084 --> 00:03:30,294
It was you.

18
00:03:31,712 --> 00:03:33,714
[grunts, breathes heavily]

19
00:03:36,425 --> 00:03:38,552
[water splashes]

20
00:04:16,632 --> 00:04:17,633
[siren blares]

21
00:04:17,716 --> 00:04:20,511
[detective] It looks like a classic case
of in-fighting gone too far.

22
00:04:20,594 --> 00:04:22,513
There's nothing more to see here,
you know.

23
00:04:23,389 --> 00:04:25,557
All right,
it's time to wrap it up quickly.

24
00:04:28,185 --> 00:04:30,354
I know who killed your father.

25
00:04:33,524 --> 00:04:34,525
Don't you wanna know?

26
00:04:37,820 --> 00:04:39,238
Then who is it?

27
00:04:43,075 --> 00:04:44,201
Oh Dollar.

28
00:04:57,756 --> 00:04:59,883
[Ju-yeong] I'll help you get revenge
for your father.

29
00:05:00,384 --> 00:05:03,804
There's a cop on the take
who has been covering for Oh Dollar.

30
00:05:05,389 --> 00:05:06,724
If you want payback,

31
00:05:08,475 --> 00:05:09,935
you've got to take him out first.

32
00:05:13,272 --> 00:05:15,024
[tires screeching]

33
00:05:18,193 --> 00:05:20,696
[breathing heavily]

34
00:05:28,620 --> 00:05:30,122
[device beeps]

35
00:05:32,958 --> 00:05:33,959
[grunts]

36
00:05:41,967 --> 00:05:43,844
Don't do something you'll regret, kid.

37
00:05:54,063 --> 00:05:55,522
[breathing shakily]

38
00:06:11,080 --> 00:06:15,209
[Dong-ju] Tear him up,
break his body, crush his bones.

39
00:06:17,086 --> 00:06:18,796
Kings never die.

40
00:06:19,505 --> 00:06:22,257
Until they destroy their enemy.

41
00:06:23,092 --> 00:06:24,218
JUSTICE

42
00:06:24,301 --> 00:06:26,762
[thug] You little shit! I'll kill you!

43
00:06:27,304 --> 00:06:28,555
[grunting]

44
00:06:38,857 --> 00:06:40,275
[Dong-ju] You're gonna die!

45
00:06:47,699 --> 00:06:48,992
- [bones crack]
- [groans]

46
00:07:02,381 --> 00:07:04,424
[upbeat music playing]

47
00:07:11,640 --> 00:07:13,350
[thug] Hey!

48
00:07:13,934 --> 00:07:16,520
[groans, grunts]

49
00:07:19,898 --> 00:07:21,942
- [Baek shouts]
- [grunts]

50
00:07:22,025 --> 00:07:23,819
You're here to save that girl, huh?

51
00:07:24,611 --> 00:07:25,737
[shouts]

52
00:07:33,120 --> 00:07:34,580
I'm gonna kill you!

53
00:07:35,539 --> 00:07:37,082
[both grunting]

54
00:07:44,882 --> 00:07:46,508
Hey, I've gotta hand it to you.

55
00:07:46,592 --> 00:07:48,969
You keep crawling back,
even though you get your ass kicked.

56
00:07:49,052 --> 00:07:50,762
I haven't come here for you, asshole.

57
00:07:58,103 --> 00:07:59,688
You bastard!

58
00:08:02,357 --> 00:08:04,067
[grunts, exclaims]

59
00:08:14,369 --> 00:08:17,497
- [screams]
- [shouts]

60
00:08:24,213 --> 00:08:25,297
[thug] There he is!

61
00:08:25,380 --> 00:08:26,715
Come here!

62
00:08:28,467 --> 00:08:29,885
[screams]

63
00:08:29,968 --> 00:08:31,136
[groans]

64
00:09:15,597 --> 00:09:16,723
[shouts]

65
00:09:17,349 --> 00:09:18,809
[Baek] Goddamn it!

66
00:09:28,318 --> 00:09:30,570
[shouts]

67
00:09:31,738 --> 00:09:32,990
[thug exclaims]

68
00:09:39,037 --> 00:09:40,038
[music stops]

69
00:09:42,374 --> 00:09:43,375
Will you calm down now?

70
00:09:43,959 --> 00:09:46,003
[yelps, grunts]

71
00:09:46,086 --> 00:09:47,170
[snickers]

72
00:09:47,254 --> 00:09:48,588
[screams]

73
00:09:49,464 --> 00:09:50,674
[both grunting]

74
00:09:55,429 --> 00:09:57,556
Do you feel sorry now?
Are you scared? Are you scared?

75
00:09:57,639 --> 00:09:59,850
Are you scared now?
I warned you, didn't I?

76
00:09:59,933 --> 00:10:01,852
I told you what would happen, you idiots.

77
00:10:01,935 --> 00:10:02,936
Hey!

78
00:10:07,399 --> 00:10:08,400
[thug exclaims]

79
00:10:14,990 --> 00:10:16,366
[pants]

80
00:10:19,453 --> 00:10:20,954
I did it. I did it.

81
00:10:21,038 --> 00:10:22,998
Dung-ju! I did it, you hear!

82
00:10:26,418 --> 00:10:27,961
Goddamn it, I'm tired of this.

83
00:10:28,712 --> 00:10:30,297
Just give it a rest!

84
00:10:33,300 --> 00:10:34,468
- [yells]
- Let's go!

85
00:10:36,428 --> 00:10:39,639
This is the last time!

86
00:10:41,558 --> 00:10:43,018
- [gasps, grunts]
- [knife slashes]

87
00:10:44,394 --> 00:10:45,437
[grunting]

88
00:11:12,964 --> 00:11:14,758
[police sirens wailing]

89
00:11:16,802 --> 00:11:18,512
All this noise.

90
00:11:24,017 --> 00:11:26,103
MAYOR

91
00:11:28,730 --> 00:11:30,649
Riot squad. Mayor, what are your orders?

92
00:11:32,609 --> 00:11:33,777
Oh.

93
00:11:33,860 --> 00:11:37,781
The thing is the reporters have
followed us, and we can't just stand by.

94
00:11:39,574 --> 00:11:40,617
Yes, sir. Will do.

95
00:11:41,284 --> 00:11:42,285
[line clicks]

96
00:11:44,037 --> 00:11:46,331
What are you waiting for?
You need to keep them out!

97
00:11:46,415 --> 00:11:48,375
You too! Get in there! Keep them out!

98
00:11:52,921 --> 00:11:54,047
[breathing shakily]

99
00:11:57,467 --> 00:11:58,552
[Leo gasps]

100
00:12:02,055 --> 00:12:03,223
Wake up.

101
00:12:03,306 --> 00:12:04,599
Come on, Leo!

102
00:12:04,683 --> 00:12:06,560
You can hear me, I know you can!

103
00:12:08,687 --> 00:12:09,813
Are…

104
00:12:10,355 --> 00:12:11,690
Are you

105
00:12:11,773 --> 00:12:13,650
going to tell me your

106
00:12:14,985 --> 00:12:16,278
real name now?

107
00:12:17,946 --> 00:12:19,072
Mi-hyang.

108
00:12:19,781 --> 00:12:20,782
Yoon Mi-hyang.

109
00:12:22,909 --> 00:12:24,244
That's an ugly name.

110
00:12:24,327 --> 00:12:25,328
[laughs]

111
00:12:28,748 --> 00:12:29,875
[coughs]

112
00:12:31,793 --> 00:12:34,838
I'm gonna remember it.

113
00:12:35,755 --> 00:12:37,048
[in Russian] Goodbye,

114
00:12:38,008 --> 00:12:39,593
my love.

115
00:12:40,969 --> 00:12:41,970
[gasps]

116
00:12:46,433 --> 00:12:47,434
[exhales weakly]

117
00:12:53,064 --> 00:12:54,065
[crying]

118
00:13:13,752 --> 00:13:14,961
[sighs]

119
00:13:18,131 --> 00:13:19,549
[grunting]

120
00:13:19,633 --> 00:13:21,176
[in English] Look at you, little shit.

121
00:13:21,259 --> 00:13:22,677
What's wrong with you?

122
00:13:22,761 --> 00:13:24,846
Why are you so scared of a blade, huh?

123
00:13:25,430 --> 00:13:27,307
I thought you used to be a fencer.

124
00:13:27,390 --> 00:13:29,226
- [glass scratches]
- Little shit!

125
00:13:37,692 --> 00:13:38,693
[groans]

126
00:13:42,697 --> 00:13:43,740
Hey.

127
00:13:44,699 --> 00:13:46,243
You came alone?

128
00:13:46,326 --> 00:13:48,119
I don't see that little mutt anywhere.

129
00:13:48,203 --> 00:13:50,747
Oh. Or maybe he's dead already? [Laughs]

130
00:13:51,665 --> 00:13:53,583
He's harder to kill than you might think.

131
00:13:53,667 --> 00:13:54,668
[Baek] He better be

132
00:13:54,751 --> 00:13:57,504
'cause I'm the one who will kill
that annoying little mutt.

133
00:13:59,881 --> 00:14:01,550
He shouldn't be underestimated.

134
00:14:02,676 --> 00:14:04,052
I hate to say it,

135
00:14:05,637 --> 00:14:08,598
he's got a hell of a lot more strength
than you give him credit for.

136
00:14:10,058 --> 00:14:11,309
I underestimated the guy

137
00:14:12,602 --> 00:14:14,229
and lost everything to that kid.

138
00:14:14,813 --> 00:14:16,273
[snickering]

139
00:14:20,235 --> 00:14:22,112
[Jong-hyeon] Yoon Dong-ju is a pain
in my ass,

140
00:14:23,405 --> 00:14:25,282
but there's one thing
I hate more, actually.

141
00:14:25,865 --> 00:14:27,158
What?

142
00:14:27,242 --> 00:14:29,327
I hate losing to anyone.

143
00:14:31,496 --> 00:14:33,873
I have sacrificed everything
in order to win.

144
00:14:33,957 --> 00:14:35,125
What the hell are you saying?

145
00:14:35,208 --> 00:14:38,420
I can't back down because
I'm just gonna feel pathetic in the end.

146
00:14:39,504 --> 00:14:41,047
I think you're losing it.

147
00:14:41,131 --> 00:14:43,300
So I've gotta stop running and just do it.

148
00:14:49,264 --> 00:14:50,473
Now let's finish this.

149
00:14:51,182 --> 00:14:52,892
- You wanna go again?
- [grunts]

150
00:14:55,061 --> 00:14:56,062
[yelps]

151
00:14:57,230 --> 00:14:58,315
[shouts]

152
00:15:07,032 --> 00:15:08,241
[groans]

153
00:15:09,492 --> 00:15:11,620
Hey, hey, hey! Wait!

154
00:15:11,703 --> 00:15:13,038
Stop it, all right? Stop!

155
00:15:13,580 --> 00:15:15,540
This isn't right. You're a cop.

156
00:15:15,624 --> 00:15:17,834
You're not supposed to go around
hitting people.

157
00:15:17,917 --> 00:15:19,210
Right?

158
00:15:19,794 --> 00:15:21,129
You came to save that girl,

159
00:15:21,212 --> 00:15:23,506
so why are you on my ass,
you goddamn leech?

160
00:15:26,426 --> 00:15:27,427
[thugs shouting]

161
00:15:50,408 --> 00:15:51,576
[elevator dings]

162
00:16:09,010 --> 00:16:10,011
[gunshots]

163
00:16:37,372 --> 00:16:38,832
Shit.

164
00:16:50,927 --> 00:16:52,095
[elevator dings]

165
00:16:53,221 --> 00:16:54,431
[elevator door opens]

166
00:16:56,725 --> 00:16:57,976
[footsteps approaching]

167
00:17:19,956 --> 00:17:20,957
[disembodied cackle]

168
00:17:33,052 --> 00:17:34,053
Shit!

169
00:17:34,137 --> 00:17:35,305
[grunts]

170
00:17:49,736 --> 00:17:51,196
[screams]

171
00:18:02,582 --> 00:18:04,667
POLICE

172
00:18:04,751 --> 00:18:06,294
[explosion]

173
00:18:13,009 --> 00:18:14,135
[thug groans]

174
00:18:14,886 --> 00:18:16,429
[panting]

175
00:18:20,266 --> 00:18:21,601
[both panting]

176
00:18:47,085 --> 00:18:48,461
[high-pitched ringing]

177
00:18:50,588 --> 00:18:51,631
[grunts]

178
00:18:54,050 --> 00:18:55,051
[groans]

179
00:18:56,219 --> 00:18:57,804
[sighs]

180
00:18:58,847 --> 00:19:00,306
- [ringing fades]
- Shit.

181
00:19:09,983 --> 00:19:10,984
[elevator dings]

182
00:19:16,364 --> 00:19:18,157
[footsteps approaching]

183
00:19:49,856 --> 00:19:50,857
Han-na!

184
00:20:38,112 --> 00:20:39,113
Hey.

185
00:20:40,782 --> 00:20:43,284
I love the gritty look.
What did I miss earlier, huh?

186
00:20:43,368 --> 00:20:45,411
[scoffs] You're not dead yet.

187
00:20:46,245 --> 00:20:48,206
No, of course not!

188
00:20:48,289 --> 00:20:49,499
I thought you knew.

189
00:20:50,667 --> 00:20:53,169
I'm not dying until your ass is in jail.

190
00:20:53,753 --> 00:20:55,129
[thug grunts]

191
00:20:57,966 --> 00:20:58,967
[thug] Hey!

192
00:21:01,511 --> 00:21:03,262
- [shouts]
- [grunting]

193
00:21:05,723 --> 00:21:07,767
You… You!

194
00:21:07,850 --> 00:21:09,185
You.

195
00:21:13,856 --> 00:21:15,233
Wait! Are you crazy?

196
00:21:15,316 --> 00:21:17,151
This is it, bastard! Go to hell!

197
00:21:17,235 --> 00:21:18,361
[shouts]

198
00:21:35,128 --> 00:21:36,129
Shit.

199
00:21:53,271 --> 00:21:54,647
- [Han-na groans]
- [Dong-ju grunts]

200
00:21:56,774 --> 00:21:57,942
[groans] Shit.

201
00:22:01,320 --> 00:22:02,321
[Dong-ju] Han-na.

202
00:22:02,905 --> 00:22:04,115
Everything okay?

203
00:22:04,198 --> 00:22:05,450
Han-na.

204
00:22:05,533 --> 00:22:06,909
Han-na!

205
00:22:06,993 --> 00:22:09,037
Han-na, can you hear me? Ji Han-na!

206
00:22:09,120 --> 00:22:10,121
Han-na!

207
00:22:11,497 --> 00:22:14,417
You don't need to shout.
You're hurting my ears.

208
00:22:18,671 --> 00:22:19,751
You sure everything's okay?

209
00:22:24,385 --> 00:22:27,221
You shouldn't have come here
all by yourself, it's dangerous.

210
00:22:30,975 --> 00:22:32,060
Seriously.

211
00:22:41,944 --> 00:22:43,029
[door opens]

212
00:22:44,822 --> 00:22:45,823
[Han-na grunts]

213
00:22:55,458 --> 00:22:56,709
Yoon Dong-ju.

214
00:22:56,793 --> 00:22:57,919
You all right?

215
00:23:02,757 --> 00:23:04,717
[Jae-Hong] Are you all right?
You're bleeding.

216
00:23:08,137 --> 00:23:10,431
Min Ju-yeong?
Where'd that piece of shit go?

217
00:23:27,031 --> 00:23:28,282
Look like she's still alive.

218
00:23:28,366 --> 00:23:30,326
Do we need an ambulance? I can call them.

219
00:24:01,440 --> 00:24:02,859
[pensive music playing]

220
00:24:07,238 --> 00:24:08,656
Nothing's broken, I think.

221
00:24:10,158 --> 00:24:12,243
- [medic] Hold still.
- [thug groans]

222
00:24:15,163 --> 00:24:16,581
- Reporting for duty.
- Oh, hey.

223
00:24:35,850 --> 00:24:39,687
[Man-sik sighs] National team or police,
it's the same story.

224
00:24:39,770 --> 00:24:42,356
You're always getting banged up. [Sighs]

225
00:24:44,317 --> 00:24:47,320
Looks like riot police and the fire crew
swept the whole building.

226
00:24:48,321 --> 00:24:50,031
Min's nowhere to be found.

227
00:24:50,114 --> 00:24:52,867
Same with the transport vehicles,
no trace of him at all.

228
00:24:52,950 --> 00:24:54,110
I bet he slipped out already.

229
00:24:54,160 --> 00:24:57,872
I think he's got more than just one or two
moles in the force, don't you think?

230
00:24:57,955 --> 00:24:59,624
I bet they're all busy hiding him.

231
00:24:59,707 --> 00:25:01,267
That's why we need to get that asshole.

232
00:25:02,793 --> 00:25:03,794
"We"?

233
00:25:04,921 --> 00:25:08,549
You're a wanted man, you understand that?
Stay out of it for Christ's sake!

234
00:25:08,633 --> 00:25:09,717
Hang on.

235
00:25:09,800 --> 00:25:12,720
How are we gonna get this little punk
outta here, any ideas?

236
00:25:13,387 --> 00:25:14,555
Moles?

237
00:25:16,015 --> 00:25:17,266
What?

238
00:25:19,060 --> 00:25:22,897
I think someone talked to Min Ju-yeong
and told him that I was here.

239
00:25:24,440 --> 00:25:25,524
His phone.

240
00:25:27,443 --> 00:25:31,280
We can find out about the mole
by checking who he talked to last.

241
00:25:33,574 --> 00:25:37,912
SAFETY IS OUR TOP PRIORITY
ON THIS CONSTRUCTION SITE

242
00:25:40,248 --> 00:25:43,000
Man, there's so much trash in there.
What a mess.

243
00:25:48,381 --> 00:25:49,507
Yeah, I heard you.

244
00:25:55,846 --> 00:25:57,348
Oh, the nausea!

245
00:25:57,431 --> 00:25:59,871
- It's my anemia. Oh, God!
- Captain! Captain! What's happening?

246
00:26:04,814 --> 00:26:06,023
You got it, sir?

247
00:26:08,484 --> 00:26:10,486
You got the phone,
so why don't you get up?

248
00:26:12,405 --> 00:26:14,031
- [grunts] Come on, sir.
- Yeah?

249
00:26:14,657 --> 00:26:16,325
God, that was nasty!

250
00:26:18,369 --> 00:26:20,579
You think they can recover the data?

251
00:26:20,663 --> 00:26:22,263
As long as the SIM card is still intact.

252
00:26:22,331 --> 00:26:24,250
I'll have the forensics chief
give it a shot.

253
00:26:24,333 --> 00:26:26,585
- What are they saying?
- [car horn honks]

254
00:26:26,669 --> 00:26:28,379
- [gates opening]
- [clamoring]

255
00:26:28,462 --> 00:26:29,463
[Jae-Hong] Captain.

256
00:26:30,006 --> 00:26:32,174
- [reporters clamoring]
- [dramatic music playing]

257
00:26:45,021 --> 00:26:46,105
What?

258
00:26:48,107 --> 00:26:49,400
[Pan-yeol clears throat]

259
00:26:49,942 --> 00:26:52,695
Oh! Good to see you, Sir! Sir.

260
00:26:52,778 --> 00:26:54,363
Listen, sir.

261
00:26:55,072 --> 00:26:56,073
Oh?

262
00:26:56,157 --> 00:26:58,909
- What, uh… happened to your jaw, sir?
- Now listen!

263
00:27:02,496 --> 00:27:04,290
[stutters] Where's Yoon Dong-ju?

264
00:27:04,874 --> 00:27:06,042
Tell me right now.

265
00:27:06,667 --> 00:27:07,960
- Oh, shit.
- [Man-sik] I'm sorry?

266
00:27:08,044 --> 00:27:10,171
Yoon Dong-ju, you dumb-ass.

267
00:27:10,254 --> 00:27:12,423
Oh. Yoon Dong-ju, sir?

268
00:27:13,174 --> 00:27:16,093
- I-I don't know, sir.
- [Pan-yeol] You don't know?

269
00:27:16,177 --> 00:27:17,178
God, this sucks.

270
00:27:17,261 --> 00:27:18,763
[Pan-yeol] Of course you'd say that!

271
00:27:21,932 --> 00:27:25,102
[scoffs] All of you little shits!

272
00:27:25,186 --> 00:27:26,812
I should've just broken his jaw.

273
00:27:26,896 --> 00:27:29,690
[Pan-yeol] You all can kiss
your damn jobs goodbye, you got that?

274
00:27:29,774 --> 00:27:33,194
And you're the first to go, you idiot!
Oh, I could just…

275
00:27:33,861 --> 00:27:36,447
Don't you move, you ungrateful worm you!

276
00:27:36,530 --> 00:27:37,948
Now stand at attention!

277
00:27:39,075 --> 00:27:40,076
Yes, sir.

278
00:27:46,582 --> 00:27:47,583
Shit, shit, shit.

279
00:27:50,294 --> 00:27:52,064
There's no more doubt that
a new type of narcotic…

280
00:27:52,088 --> 00:27:54,465
[sighs] It's a total bust, isn't it?

281
00:27:55,257 --> 00:27:57,444
- What the hell is happening here?
- The operation was carried out

282
00:27:57,468 --> 00:27:59,188
- under Insung Police Commissioner…
- Goddamn.

283
00:27:59,261 --> 00:28:01,865
Who launched a large-scale crackdown
with support from the riot police.

284
00:28:01,889 --> 00:28:02,890
[vehicle approaching]

285
00:28:03,641 --> 00:28:04,642
Hey, hey, hey.

286
00:28:13,317 --> 00:28:14,777
- What the hell happened?
- Goddamn it.

287
00:28:14,860 --> 00:28:16,153
You saw the news?

288
00:28:17,405 --> 00:28:18,965
This is out of control, what's going on?

289
00:28:18,989 --> 00:28:21,826
It's all blowing up on the news,
and Min's MIA.

290
00:28:21,909 --> 00:28:24,495
You look like you got your ass beat again.
What happened to you?

291
00:28:24,578 --> 00:28:26,455
Shut up, you idiot!

292
00:28:26,539 --> 00:28:28,433
The thing is we couldn't get
half of our product out

293
00:28:28,457 --> 00:28:30,918
because you dragged your fucking ass
sending the trucks!

294
00:28:35,881 --> 00:28:37,007
[sighs] Shit!

295
00:28:38,092 --> 00:28:39,635
[car engine revving]

296
00:28:40,344 --> 00:28:41,345
[tires screech]

297
00:28:45,349 --> 00:28:46,600
[subordinate] Hey, boss.

298
00:28:46,684 --> 00:28:48,727
What's the deal? Did you find out?

299
00:28:48,811 --> 00:28:50,396
I couldn't get a hold of anyone.

300
00:28:50,479 --> 00:28:52,148
And Min Ju-Yeong has fucking disappeared

301
00:28:52,231 --> 00:28:53,566
[sighs]

302
00:28:55,109 --> 00:28:57,445
And now
we look like a bunch of clowns, huh?

303
00:28:59,905 --> 00:29:01,740
So what do we do about the product, boss?

304
00:29:06,537 --> 00:29:08,622
It's worth hundreds of billions of won…

305
00:29:11,584 --> 00:29:13,294
If we off-load it at a cheap price.

306
00:29:16,380 --> 00:29:17,965
Min's gone dark as far as we know.

307
00:29:19,758 --> 00:29:21,760
And now the cook's dead and gone,

308
00:29:21,844 --> 00:29:24,180
as well as that rat
who was gonna take it all.

309
00:29:24,263 --> 00:29:26,390
Which means the only guy
who knows that we have it…

310
00:29:28,476 --> 00:29:29,894
Is here with you and me.

311
00:29:35,691 --> 00:29:37,318
Hey, where are the goods?

312
00:29:38,360 --> 00:29:40,070
Okay, understood.

313
00:29:40,154 --> 00:29:42,907
Oh, and how many guys can you round up
right now?

314
00:29:44,283 --> 00:29:47,036
Yeah, it's urgent.
Just get everyone you can, all right?

315
00:29:48,078 --> 00:29:49,413
Okay, I'll call you later.

316
00:29:49,997 --> 00:29:50,998
[door opens]

317
00:29:51,999 --> 00:29:53,417
Oh, shit.

318
00:30:06,305 --> 00:30:07,681
You going somewhere?

319
00:30:14,021 --> 00:30:15,147
Is this a prank?

320
00:30:17,024 --> 00:30:18,692
For God's sake.

321
00:30:24,156 --> 00:30:25,824
You should be careful, kid.

322
00:30:25,908 --> 00:30:27,952
You know I'm a heavyweight champion.

323
00:30:28,661 --> 00:30:29,745
Don't mess with me.

324
00:30:29,828 --> 00:30:30,829
[scoffs]

325
00:30:49,723 --> 00:30:52,723
- It's your fingerprint that unlocks it.
- [automated voice] The door is open.

326
00:30:53,102 --> 00:30:55,145
- [Man-sik] Hey.
- Oh. Hey, Dad!

327
00:30:56,230 --> 00:30:58,732
Aw, sweet Jeong-a, watching the news,
worrying about her dad.

328
00:30:58,816 --> 00:30:59,817
What are you saying?

329
00:30:59,900 --> 00:31:01,777
Some braised chicken for you!

330
00:31:01,860 --> 00:31:03,654
- [chuckles]
- Oh. It's braised chicken?

331
00:31:04,154 --> 00:31:06,240
Oh, sweet. I could eat all of it.

332
00:31:06,323 --> 00:31:08,033
Yeah, you'd like that. Wouldn't you?

333
00:31:08,117 --> 00:31:10,869
You lie around the house,
doing absolutely nothing worth mentioning.

334
00:31:10,953 --> 00:31:13,139
Hey, guys. What are you waiting for?
Get in. We've been through hell.

335
00:31:13,163 --> 00:31:14,748
We deserve some food, at least.

336
00:31:15,249 --> 00:31:17,126
- Hi, Jeong-a.
- [Jeong-a] Oh.

337
00:31:17,209 --> 00:31:19,646
[Man-sik] You remember them, right?
Say hi. These are my colleagues.

338
00:31:19,670 --> 00:31:21,672
And this is my daughter, Go Jeong-a.

339
00:31:23,424 --> 00:31:24,800
[Jong-hyeon] I'm sorry to intrude.

340
00:31:25,801 --> 00:31:28,012
[romantic music playing]

341
00:31:28,804 --> 00:31:30,139
Hello.

342
00:31:32,641 --> 00:31:33,961
[Man-sik] Hey, take some chicken!

343
00:31:34,018 --> 00:31:35,102
- Cheers.
- [Jong-hyeon sighs]

344
00:31:35,185 --> 00:31:37,313
- Good work today.
- [Jae-Hong] Good work today, guys.

345
00:31:43,319 --> 00:31:44,320
[Dong-ju] Whoa.

346
00:31:44,903 --> 00:31:47,573
Wrap it in aged kimchi first.
It's insanely good.

347
00:31:47,656 --> 00:31:50,534
I had it with Jeong-a pretty recently
and I still think about it.

348
00:31:51,619 --> 00:31:53,621
You just wrap it like this and…

349
00:31:57,041 --> 00:31:58,542
It's so good, right?

350
00:31:59,126 --> 00:32:01,128
- This is pretty good.
- It's really that good?

351
00:32:02,004 --> 00:32:04,006
I like this one better, it's more tender.

352
00:32:07,468 --> 00:32:08,469
Mmm…

353
00:32:08,552 --> 00:32:10,012
You say it's very tender?

354
00:32:12,097 --> 00:32:14,516
[Man-sik] Ji, I've gotta say
I'm a little hurt, you know.

355
00:32:15,100 --> 00:32:17,895
I just mean, regarding your dad.
I was totally unaware.

356
00:32:17,978 --> 00:32:20,373
You should've given us a heads-up
at some point, don't you think?

357
00:32:20,397 --> 00:32:22,941
Why'd you keep that bottled up
for so long?

358
00:32:23,025 --> 00:32:25,611
I'm just…
I'm just a little bit hurt, okay?

359
00:32:25,694 --> 00:32:26,945
I'm sorry about that.

360
00:32:27,029 --> 00:32:29,657
Han-na had to suffer through this,
why are you going after her?

361
00:32:29,740 --> 00:32:31,325
Let's try and get that bastard instead.

362
00:32:31,408 --> 00:32:33,261
Will you stop talking
about "getting that bastard"?

363
00:32:33,285 --> 00:32:35,037
- Try some.
- You're still on the wanted list.

364
00:32:35,120 --> 00:32:37,599
And you're staying home until we've dealt
with the matter, you understand?

365
00:32:37,623 --> 00:32:39,333
- Stay out of it, punk.
- [smacks lips]

366
00:32:39,917 --> 00:32:41,502
So what's the plan now, sir?

367
00:32:42,086 --> 00:32:43,671
We catch him, of course.

368
00:32:43,754 --> 00:32:44,838
Yeah, we do.

369
00:32:44,922 --> 00:32:47,150
Thing is, the prosecution has
joined forces with the police.

370
00:32:47,174 --> 00:32:49,343
So it's gonna be hard for us to step in.

371
00:32:49,426 --> 00:32:53,639
- We're not gonna get any backup either.
- So then it's just us, the RIU,

372
00:32:53,722 --> 00:32:56,558
and if we're lucky,
Senior Inspector Kang from Seobu Station?

373
00:32:57,810 --> 00:33:00,104
Kang won't be able to help us, I think.

374
00:33:00,813 --> 00:33:03,649
I'm sure their hands are tied,
and they've been disciplined already.

375
00:33:06,026 --> 00:33:09,571
So it's just gonna be us
with the RIU, hopefully.

376
00:33:10,072 --> 00:33:11,073
But, still…

377
00:33:11,699 --> 00:33:14,743
Stop it, will you? Stop eating,
I'm talking about something important!

378
00:33:14,827 --> 00:33:15,911
[groans]

379
00:33:17,538 --> 00:33:18,539
[Man-sik] Huh?

380
00:33:18,622 --> 00:33:19,998
You being weird again?

381
00:33:20,082 --> 00:33:23,669
Didn't I tell you to quit doing that?
Where'd you even pick up this nonsense?

382
00:33:23,752 --> 00:33:26,046
- It's Lamaze breathing.
- "Lama"?

383
00:33:26,130 --> 00:33:28,048
[Jae-Hong] No, Lamaze breathing.

384
00:33:28,132 --> 00:33:30,551
You calm down your nerves
by breathing that way.

385
00:33:30,634 --> 00:33:33,387
I know because my wife used to do it
when she was pregnant.

386
00:33:34,346 --> 00:33:35,806
[quirky music playing]

387
00:33:48,777 --> 00:33:51,613
- Don't tell me you're…
- [hiccups]

388
00:33:51,697 --> 00:33:52,865
[hiccups]

389
00:33:52,948 --> 00:33:54,241
[both hiccup]

390
00:33:58,036 --> 00:33:59,121
Wait, Jeong-a!

391
00:34:00,122 --> 00:34:01,582
Jeong-a, open the door!

392
00:34:01,665 --> 00:34:04,001
Just talk to me, okay? Hey, open up.

393
00:34:04,084 --> 00:34:06,712
Is that the reason you fought
with your mother and came back here?

394
00:34:07,296 --> 00:34:08,422
Come on, Jeong-A. Open up!

395
00:34:09,298 --> 00:34:11,300
The Captain's gonna be okay, right?

396
00:34:11,383 --> 00:34:13,552
I shouldn't have said anything
about the breathing.

397
00:34:13,635 --> 00:34:15,179
- It's okay.
- [Jong-hyeon sighs]

398
00:34:16,180 --> 00:34:17,639
Is your hand okay?

399
00:34:17,723 --> 00:34:20,350
Oh, also, you sure
none of you need to go to the hospital?

400
00:34:21,101 --> 00:34:22,728
Oh, I'm okay.

401
00:34:25,481 --> 00:34:26,857
We're all right, yeah.

402
00:34:26,940 --> 00:34:28,400
Okay, then, why don't we head out?

403
00:34:28,984 --> 00:34:30,944
I've never wanted to go home
more than I do now.

404
00:34:31,028 --> 00:34:32,279
Sounds good.

405
00:34:32,362 --> 00:34:34,215
I can give you a ride,
we're heading the same way.

406
00:34:34,239 --> 00:34:35,282
Oh, that'd be great.

407
00:34:35,783 --> 00:34:36,825
And you two?

408
00:34:38,368 --> 00:34:40,208
All right, good night then.
See you both later.

409
00:34:42,372 --> 00:34:43,457
[Jae-Hong grunts]

410
00:34:43,540 --> 00:34:45,501
- Let's do a group hug.
- Let's just go.

411
00:34:45,584 --> 00:34:46,877
- Oh, okay.
- [Han-na chuckles]

412
00:34:46,960 --> 00:34:47,961
Later.

413
00:34:48,962 --> 00:34:50,339
[gentle music playing]

414
00:35:00,098 --> 00:35:01,099
[sighs]

415
00:35:12,194 --> 00:35:13,904
- [door closes]
- [chattering on TV]

416
00:35:16,240 --> 00:35:18,826
[clears throat]
Hey, sweetie, I'm back now.

417
00:35:18,909 --> 00:35:21,203
I'm sorry.
You must've been really worried.

418
00:35:21,286 --> 00:35:22,472
[newscaster] There are still reports

419
00:35:22,496 --> 00:35:25,374
of the dangerous new synthetic drug
showing up around the city,

420
00:35:25,457 --> 00:35:28,210
and the commissioner urges caution
in dealing with strangers

421
00:35:28,293 --> 00:35:31,046
or questionable individuals,
who could be drug dealers.

422
00:35:33,507 --> 00:35:34,675
Hey, you know what?

423
00:35:38,011 --> 00:35:40,639
That bronze medal has always
made me feel ashamed.

424
00:35:41,723 --> 00:35:43,600
Felt like I didn't give it my all.

425
00:35:44,226 --> 00:35:46,103
Like I didn't try hard enough
my whole life.

426
00:35:46,687 --> 00:35:49,439
That's why I could never show it
to our kids with pride.

427
00:35:50,649 --> 00:35:51,650
Hmm?

428
00:35:52,401 --> 00:35:53,402
- [grunts]
- [groans]

429
00:35:54,361 --> 00:35:59,074
Listen, not once have our kids ever been
ashamed of their father, you hear me?

430
00:35:59,157 --> 00:36:02,327
You should've seen how happy they were
to get to watch you on the news.

431
00:36:02,953 --> 00:36:06,248
Whatever you decide to do,
we're always on your side,

432
00:36:06,331 --> 00:36:08,208
always here to support you.

433
00:36:09,918 --> 00:36:11,628
- Oh, God. [Yelps]
- Oh, come on!

434
00:36:11,712 --> 00:36:12,921
- Don't cry!
- Stop!

435
00:36:13,505 --> 00:36:14,590
This must've hurt.

436
00:36:15,507 --> 00:36:16,508
Okay, wait.

437
00:36:19,845 --> 00:36:20,845
Here.

438
00:36:23,307 --> 00:36:25,142
- Dong-ju.
- Hmm?

439
00:36:26,059 --> 00:36:28,770
You know, you were unconscious
for two days straight.

440
00:36:33,650 --> 00:36:35,193
I know you were concerned.

441
00:36:36,486 --> 00:36:38,739
You need hospital care.
I'll find a safe one for you.

442
00:36:38,822 --> 00:36:40,365
Actually, I'm totally fine.

443
00:36:40,449 --> 00:36:43,493
All that sleep must've worked wonders.
I do feel a lot better.

444
00:36:47,331 --> 00:36:48,540
I think you should know

445
00:36:49,791 --> 00:36:52,669
I really wish you would
take better care of yourself.

446
00:36:53,211 --> 00:36:55,464
[soft music playing]

447
00:36:55,547 --> 00:36:57,674
And stop bottling up all your pain.

448
00:37:01,720 --> 00:37:02,763
Uh…

449
00:37:02,846 --> 00:37:04,348
All right, I hear you.

450
00:37:06,016 --> 00:37:08,977
But first, you're my patient.

451
00:37:12,606 --> 00:37:14,900
It's not that bad, don't overdo it, okay?

452
00:37:14,983 --> 00:37:17,861
No, no. It'll leave a scar
if we don't treat it.

453
00:37:17,945 --> 00:37:19,529
Let me handle it.

454
00:37:19,613 --> 00:37:22,532
You should know that I'm a pro at this.

455
00:37:24,743 --> 00:37:26,954
Anyway, you belong in a hospital
more than I do.

456
00:37:27,537 --> 00:37:29,164
Okay, I hear you. [Chuckles]

457
00:37:30,499 --> 00:37:31,500
All right.

458
00:37:39,633 --> 00:37:40,633
All done.

459
00:37:41,510 --> 00:37:43,762
Ooh. Why are you so good at this?

460
00:37:48,350 --> 00:37:49,393
Well,

461
00:37:50,769 --> 00:37:52,270
did I ever tell you

462
00:37:55,857 --> 00:37:58,276
that I got beat up a lot when I was a kid?

463
00:37:59,653 --> 00:38:02,322
It was just that my father
was drinking a lot, you know,

464
00:38:02,406 --> 00:38:04,741
and so he would hit me and my mother.

465
00:38:06,284 --> 00:38:09,287
The only thing I was able to do for her
was stuff like this.

466
00:38:10,539 --> 00:38:12,249
Trying to cover her wounds…

467
00:38:12,958 --> 00:38:15,711
[inhales deeply, blows]

468
00:38:16,753 --> 00:38:17,838
…and doing this.

469
00:38:18,630 --> 00:38:20,716
It's 'cause I'm used to it. Now you know.

470
00:38:29,891 --> 00:38:30,891
What?

471
00:38:31,852 --> 00:38:34,021
It's nothing. I'm just proud of you.

472
00:38:36,648 --> 00:38:37,733
How about a reward?

473
00:38:39,735 --> 00:38:41,820
Just go get changed you goofball.

474
00:38:41,903 --> 00:38:44,573
What for?
I'm gonna take 'em off again in a sec.

475
00:38:45,490 --> 00:38:46,700
Huh?

476
00:38:47,743 --> 00:38:49,036
Oh! [Gasps]

477
00:39:00,172 --> 00:39:02,340
[gentle music playing]

478
00:39:28,575 --> 00:39:29,910
- [door lock beeps]
- [music stops]

479
00:39:30,494 --> 00:39:32,013
- [door knob rattles]
- [Gyeong-suk] Oh, God!

480
00:39:32,037 --> 00:39:33,639
- [sobbing] Han-na! Han-na!
- [grunts] Come.

481
00:39:33,663 --> 00:39:35,332
- Huh? [Grunts]
- Come on. You have to...

482
00:39:35,415 --> 00:39:37,167
- Han-na, are you in there?
- Shit.

483
00:39:37,250 --> 00:39:39,377
- I just need the pa-passcode.
- [door lock beeping]

484
00:39:39,461 --> 00:39:43,423
Ugh, no! Why isn't it working?
Oh, my goodness. [Sobbing]

485
00:39:43,507 --> 00:39:45,067
- [Han-na] Oh! No, not here.
- Then where?

486
00:39:45,092 --> 00:39:46,635
The bathroom, go in there.

487
00:39:46,718 --> 00:39:49,429
- [panting]
- [Gyeong-suk] Pull yourself together.

488
00:39:49,513 --> 00:39:52,724
You're strong, you're a mother!
You're a mother! Han-na! Han-na!

489
00:39:52,808 --> 00:39:55,769
Hold on. Han-na! [Sobbing]

490
00:39:55,852 --> 00:39:56,853
[lock beeping continues]

491
00:39:56,937 --> 00:39:58,980
God, I just wanna open the door!

492
00:39:59,689 --> 00:40:03,193
Oh, my God! Oh, my God!
Wait, did you change the passcode?

493
00:40:03,276 --> 00:40:06,279
Oh, God, are you all right?
Come on, let me look at you, honey.

494
00:40:06,363 --> 00:40:08,031
[sobbing]

495
00:40:08,115 --> 00:40:10,200
Thank God you're okay.

496
00:40:10,283 --> 00:40:12,786
- Yeah, all right. All right. It's okay.
- Let me look at you.

497
00:40:12,869 --> 00:40:15,872
[gasping] What happened to your face?

498
00:40:15,956 --> 00:40:17,916
It's nothing. It's just a scratch.

499
00:40:17,999 --> 00:40:18,834
Why are you here?

500
00:40:18,917 --> 00:40:21,169
Han-na, my heart was pounding
when I saw the news!

501
00:40:21,253 --> 00:40:22,462
Of course I came running!

502
00:40:22,546 --> 00:40:24,381
Why on Earth weren't you
answering your phone?

503
00:40:24,464 --> 00:40:26,925
You scared the hell out of me!

504
00:40:27,008 --> 00:40:29,928
So it's just your face?
You're not hurt anywhere else?

505
00:40:30,011 --> 00:40:32,139
- Oh, my God, look.
- No, I'm fine. I'm fine.

506
00:40:32,222 --> 00:40:34,474
[Han-na] I said I'm fine,
so calm down, okay?

507
00:40:34,558 --> 00:40:36,726
[Gyeong-suk] No, honey, you're not fine!

508
00:40:37,310 --> 00:40:38,562
Oh, my goodness.

509
00:40:39,354 --> 00:40:40,814
Oh, no.

510
00:40:41,648 --> 00:40:43,859
Why is your face so hot?

511
00:40:43,942 --> 00:40:46,486
What? It's not hot. Mom, it's like always.

512
00:40:46,570 --> 00:40:48,822
Oh, wait, just a minute.
Oh God, what do I do?

513
00:40:48,905 --> 00:40:51,449
- Oh, maybe I can just...
- [Han-na groaning]

514
00:40:51,533 --> 00:40:55,203
Oh, no, honey! Are you okay? What's wrong?
Are you in pain? What's going on, honey?

515
00:40:55,287 --> 00:40:57,974
I've just got a bit of a headache.
I don't think I'm feeling too well.

516
00:40:57,998 --> 00:40:59,875
Oh dear, where does it hurt?
I'm so worried.

517
00:40:59,958 --> 00:41:01,644
- Oh, God. Oh, God.
- Would you just help me get to my room?

518
00:41:01,668 --> 00:41:03,521
- If you could?
- All right, hold on to me, hold on to me.

519
00:41:03,545 --> 00:41:05,463
I'll bring you there.
That's it, very good.

520
00:41:05,547 --> 00:41:08,133
Good, lean on me, that's it,
we're slowly getting there.

521
00:41:08,216 --> 00:41:11,136
What's your dad doing up there
if he's not protecting you?

522
00:41:11,219 --> 00:41:15,056
Oh, dear God.
I can't believe this is happening.

523
00:41:23,106 --> 00:41:24,399
Ugh, seriously?

524
00:41:26,568 --> 00:41:28,445
[exclaims] Oh, shit.

525
00:41:29,696 --> 00:41:30,989
Geez.

526
00:41:31,698 --> 00:41:34,701
- [neighbor] Seeing the young lady, huh?
- [cooing, giggling]

527
00:41:34,784 --> 00:41:36,578
- Mm-hmm.
- Where are you going?

528
00:41:36,661 --> 00:41:37,829
DUNG-JU

529
00:41:37,913 --> 00:41:39,372
- Shh, shh, shh.
- Oh, he's hot!

530
00:41:54,971 --> 00:41:56,097
[door bell rings]

531
00:41:58,141 --> 00:41:59,309
[knock on door]

532
00:42:00,602 --> 00:42:02,270
[door bell continues ringing]

533
00:42:05,190 --> 00:42:06,900
FRONT DOOR

534
00:42:06,983 --> 00:42:08,568
CALL

535
00:42:09,945 --> 00:42:12,530
[sing-song] Kim Jong-hyeon,
how you been? [Chuckles]

536
00:42:13,073 --> 00:42:15,492
Aren't you home? I think you are, right?

537
00:42:15,575 --> 00:42:18,620
Could you just let me in, please?
Come on, Jong-hyeon?

538
00:42:19,871 --> 00:42:21,164
Hey.

539
00:42:23,541 --> 00:42:24,960
[automated voice] The door is open.

540
00:42:25,710 --> 00:42:27,462
[sighs] You been to a sauna?

541
00:42:29,214 --> 00:42:30,257
Stop smiling.

542
00:42:36,221 --> 00:42:37,847
Sorry to bother you.

543
00:42:39,474 --> 00:42:41,017
[automated voice] The door is locked.

544
00:42:45,772 --> 00:42:47,857
SÃO PAULO 2018
KIM JONG-HYEON WINS SILVER

545
00:42:49,150 --> 00:42:50,485
Need a hand with that?

546
00:42:51,403 --> 00:42:52,404
You moving?

547
00:42:58,910 --> 00:43:01,830
None of your business.
And stop pretending we're friends.

548
00:43:05,166 --> 00:43:06,167
[huffs]

549
00:43:30,108 --> 00:43:31,943
So let me ask you a question.

550
00:43:32,902 --> 00:43:35,030
When'd you start hating me?
I always wondered.

551
00:43:35,613 --> 00:43:36,614
From the start.

552
00:43:38,199 --> 00:43:39,284
Why?

553
00:43:41,661 --> 00:43:43,163
I didn't like how you smiled.

554
00:43:44,664 --> 00:43:47,334
- [Jong-hyeon] Yoon Dong-ju?
- [friend] Yeah. Do you know him?

555
00:43:47,417 --> 00:43:49,669
That crazy boxer
who just made the national team.

556
00:43:49,753 --> 00:43:51,314
Apparently, he's hooked
on the superstition

557
00:43:51,338 --> 00:43:53,882
that if you run 100 laps here,
you'll win gold.

558
00:43:53,965 --> 00:43:56,926
Man, the guy's been going for a week,
every single day.

559
00:43:57,010 --> 00:43:59,220
I guess no one's been able
to go past lap 94,

560
00:43:59,304 --> 00:44:01,431
but I think he's gonna make it to 100.

561
00:44:01,514 --> 00:44:03,308
He's already on lap 99.

562
00:44:03,391 --> 00:44:04,934
VICTORY GYM
I AM KING

563
00:44:07,562 --> 00:44:09,773
Look at that sweat, my God.
Dong-ju, let's get it!

564
00:44:09,856 --> 00:44:12,776
- Come on, Yoon, almost there!
- [crowd cheering]

565
00:44:12,859 --> 00:44:14,778
Wow! Yoon Dong-ju, you've got it!

566
00:44:14,861 --> 00:44:16,279
[cheering continues]

567
00:44:22,869 --> 00:44:24,996
Let's go! Yeah!

568
00:44:31,127 --> 00:44:33,213
SOAR TOWARD VICTORY
TEAM KOREA

569
00:44:34,255 --> 00:44:35,590
- See you later.
- All right.

570
00:44:36,257 --> 00:44:40,470
Wow, that's really impressive.
He's killing it, man.

571
00:44:56,319 --> 00:44:58,947
I didn't like your smile,
and I still don't.

572
00:45:02,075 --> 00:45:03,910
Well, you're not my favorite either.

573
00:45:05,870 --> 00:45:07,247
Just go to sleep.

574
00:45:20,552 --> 00:45:21,636
Good night.

575
00:45:30,103 --> 00:45:32,105
[Dong-ju vomiting, coughing]

576
00:45:41,197 --> 00:45:42,407
[water running]

577
00:45:43,158 --> 00:45:44,868
[retches, spits]

578
00:45:45,493 --> 00:45:46,494
[gasps]

579
00:45:48,371 --> 00:45:49,372
[groans, winces]

580
00:45:54,711 --> 00:45:55,795
[toilet flushes]

581
00:45:56,838 --> 00:45:57,839
[groans]

582
00:46:04,846 --> 00:46:06,723
So we still don't where Min Ju-yeong is?

583
00:46:06,806 --> 00:46:07,682
Nah.

584
00:46:07,765 --> 00:46:10,810
Traffic cams got those Russian Mafia guys
escaping from the scene,

585
00:46:10,894 --> 00:46:12,770
as well as those Korean-Chinese guys,

586
00:46:13,313 --> 00:46:15,857
but how the Hell did Min Ju-yeong get out?
Nobody knows.

587
00:46:16,733 --> 00:46:20,528
The way out of Goldengate Central
is that way. No one can get around it.

588
00:46:21,654 --> 00:46:23,740
There's no shot at escaping from here

589
00:46:23,823 --> 00:46:26,034
if someone didn't have
an inside connection.

590
00:46:26,117 --> 00:46:29,704
[sighs] Yeah, we need to find out
who that mole is, for real.

591
00:46:31,706 --> 00:46:33,684
There's some good news,
we seized a truck yesterday.

592
00:46:33,708 --> 00:46:35,418
And it belongs to our man Oh Jong-go.

593
00:46:36,085 --> 00:46:37,605
The other trucks showed up on camera too,

594
00:46:37,629 --> 00:46:40,173
but their plates were unreadable,
unfortunately.

595
00:46:40,256 --> 00:46:42,634
Looks like they were all used
to transport Candy.

596
00:46:43,259 --> 00:46:45,428
That's great work.
Can you send me these photos?

597
00:46:45,512 --> 00:46:48,056
- We can handle it and go after Jong-Gu.
- Sure thing.

598
00:46:50,975 --> 00:46:53,811
By the way,
is everything all right with those two?

599
00:46:55,730 --> 00:46:56,981
[wind whistling]

600
00:46:58,650 --> 00:47:02,570
Did you stay up all night
because of the... the thing with Jeong-a?

601
00:47:04,197 --> 00:47:05,657
My daughter's…

602
00:47:07,700 --> 00:47:09,744
- Not pregnant.
- [gasps]

603
00:47:09,827 --> 00:47:10,828
Oh!

604
00:47:11,788 --> 00:47:14,040
Oh, thank God. I was so worried.
[chuckling]

605
00:47:14,123 --> 00:47:16,709
My wife, she's the one who's pregnant.

606
00:47:16,793 --> 00:47:18,586
Ah, your wife… Wait?

607
00:47:19,170 --> 00:47:21,714
[laughs] Congratulations!

608
00:47:22,465 --> 00:47:25,343
Oh wow, I didn't know you even
still had it in you, sir.

609
00:47:25,426 --> 00:47:28,471
I guess you've been eating well
without us, huh? [Laughing]

610
00:47:30,890 --> 00:47:32,767
It's not my kid.

611
00:47:32,850 --> 00:47:34,269
[laughing stops]

612
00:47:34,352 --> 00:47:35,352
I'm snipped.

613
00:47:36,729 --> 00:47:37,772
Uh…

614
00:47:38,565 --> 00:47:41,067
Yeah, but she would have
to cheat for that... [gasps]

615
00:47:45,280 --> 00:47:49,284
[wailing] My heart's been broken!
She's gone with the wind!

616
00:47:49,367 --> 00:47:50,535
Gone, forever!

617
00:47:50,618 --> 00:47:52,161
- [Jong-hyeon] Let's go.
- [wailing]

618
00:47:52,245 --> 00:47:55,331
Kim, I'll ride with you, okay?
Uh, why won't this thing open? Hey!

619
00:47:55,415 --> 00:47:57,166
Kim, don't you leave me, please!

620
00:47:57,250 --> 00:47:59,669
INSUNG METROPOLITAN POLICE AGENCY

621
00:47:59,752 --> 00:48:01,462
Well, you're right on time.

622
00:48:07,343 --> 00:48:10,513
- I'm grateful you let me borrow your car.
- And what else?

623
00:48:10,597 --> 00:48:14,309
[chuckles] And also,
I'm grateful for everything you've done.

624
00:48:15,393 --> 00:48:18,372
So I'm supposed to help you again?
There has to be somebody else you can ask.

625
00:48:18,396 --> 00:48:20,106
Well, there is no one, I'm sorry.

626
00:48:20,189 --> 00:48:23,151
You're the only person
who will even speak to me in here.

627
00:48:23,234 --> 00:48:24,819
Okay, so what?

628
00:48:24,902 --> 00:48:26,904
And so I should just do this for you? Why?

629
00:48:26,988 --> 00:48:28,531
You like me, that's one reason.

630
00:48:28,615 --> 00:48:31,159
You think that?
I'm sorry, but you're mistaken!

631
00:48:31,242 --> 00:48:33,828
All right, even if I'm mistaken,
I need your help.

632
00:48:33,911 --> 00:48:36,497
I'm all out of people I'm able to trust.

633
00:48:37,081 --> 00:48:39,626
And I'm sorry. All of this is my fault.

634
00:48:39,709 --> 00:48:41,169
Don't sweat it, okay?

635
00:48:42,086 --> 00:48:44,047
I'm gonna just get comfortable
and watch TV

636
00:48:44,130 --> 00:48:46,215
for the next three months. [Chuckles]

637
00:48:46,299 --> 00:48:47,300
Ah.

638
00:48:50,637 --> 00:48:53,348
I couldn't just walk out
without picking this up for you.

639
00:48:55,141 --> 00:48:58,936
It's everyone who was present at
the joint task force launch ceremony.

640
00:48:59,646 --> 00:49:01,522
Could be useful for your investigation.

641
00:49:02,106 --> 00:49:04,275
[sighs] Why would you do all this?

642
00:49:05,610 --> 00:49:08,321
Well, you were right about it.
Yes, I like you.

643
00:49:11,699 --> 00:49:13,743
Now you know. But really…

644
00:49:14,494 --> 00:49:16,162
I've also been a little jealous.

645
00:49:16,663 --> 00:49:18,331
I always had that dream you know.

646
00:49:18,414 --> 00:49:21,751
To get a chance to be a badass
out there in the field. [Laughs]

647
00:49:22,502 --> 00:49:24,796
I'm living my dream vicariously
through you.

648
00:49:25,380 --> 00:49:26,381
Yeah, it's like…

649
00:49:28,341 --> 00:49:29,967
You're some big TV star

650
00:49:30,051 --> 00:49:33,137
and all I can think is,
"I wanna be like her!" [chuckles]

651
00:49:33,638 --> 00:49:34,639
[chuckles]

652
00:49:36,933 --> 00:49:40,520
J9 SECURITY

653
00:49:40,603 --> 00:49:41,854
Ah, shit.

654
00:49:41,938 --> 00:49:43,856
Everything's already been cleared out.

655
00:49:52,907 --> 00:49:54,283
[Man-sik] Is he here?

656
00:49:54,367 --> 00:49:55,952
Seems like it's been empty for a while.

657
00:49:56,035 --> 00:49:57,620
Even the power's been cut.

658
00:49:57,704 --> 00:49:59,038
[Man-sik groans] These bastards.

659
00:50:04,043 --> 00:50:05,253
[sighs]

660
00:50:05,336 --> 00:50:06,656
These aren't the right ones here.

661
00:50:06,713 --> 00:50:08,393
The plates don't match
any of these trucks.

662
00:50:08,464 --> 00:50:10,174
And the containers don't match either.

663
00:50:10,675 --> 00:50:12,510
Sir, I called the district office,

664
00:50:12,593 --> 00:50:14,804
they told me about some junkyard
that deals specifically

665
00:50:14,887 --> 00:50:16,973
with cargo truck deregistration
and replacements.

666
00:50:17,056 --> 00:50:20,727
I think Oh used plates from trucks
that had been illegally deregistered.

667
00:50:21,686 --> 00:50:23,312
All right, let's go have a look.

668
00:50:27,942 --> 00:50:30,254
- You want it? How much do you want it?
- Ooh, I want it all.

669
00:50:30,278 --> 00:50:31,988
- [giggles]
- Hello, Mr. Lee Yong-ju.

670
00:50:32,905 --> 00:50:34,741
- What the hell? Ah, shit.
- Oh!

671
00:50:36,033 --> 00:50:37,034
Oh.

672
00:50:38,202 --> 00:50:39,537
That's 'cause he took the train.

673
00:50:39,620 --> 00:50:41,664
She was with Oh Jong-go.
She's the bookkeeper.

674
00:50:41,748 --> 00:50:42,749
Ah.

675
00:50:43,332 --> 00:50:45,626
Who are they? Your father and brother?

676
00:50:49,005 --> 00:50:50,298
[whispers] They're police.

677
00:50:52,550 --> 00:50:53,718
Ah, shit.

678
00:50:53,801 --> 00:50:55,470
Whoa, whoa, whoa.

679
00:50:55,553 --> 00:50:56,971
[quirky music playing]

680
00:50:57,054 --> 00:50:58,055
[grunts]

681
00:50:59,515 --> 00:51:02,018
[grunts] Shit. Shit.

682
00:51:03,811 --> 00:51:04,872
- Ooh. Whoa.
- [Yong-ju] Damn it.

683
00:51:04,896 --> 00:51:06,647
What, you got somewhere to be?
I wanna know.

684
00:51:10,193 --> 00:51:12,779
- [exclaims] Damn it.
- [grunts]

685
00:51:13,863 --> 00:51:15,323
- [groans]
- [thuds]

686
00:51:15,406 --> 00:51:16,866
Oh, shit.

687
00:51:16,949 --> 00:51:18,242
- [Yong-ju] Look at this.
- Oh?

688
00:51:18,326 --> 00:51:20,077
Ah, just put it down.

689
00:51:20,620 --> 00:51:22,121
Go on.

690
00:51:24,123 --> 00:51:26,167
[yelps]

691
00:51:26,250 --> 00:51:29,420
Look, we know you've been selling
Mr. Oh plates for his cargo trucks.

692
00:51:29,504 --> 00:51:31,172
And I want those plate numbers.

693
00:51:31,255 --> 00:51:32,757
Dude, I don't know.

694
00:51:32,840 --> 00:51:33,841
I've got tons of clients.

695
00:51:33,925 --> 00:51:36,385
There's so many plates I've put on
hundreds of trucks.

696
00:51:36,469 --> 00:51:37,696
You might as well just arrest me.

697
00:51:37,720 --> 00:51:39,806
I'll pay a fine and be done with it.

698
00:51:40,389 --> 00:51:41,641
You came all this way for this?

699
00:51:41,724 --> 00:51:43,702
Just to embarrass me
over this nonsense. Seriously?

700
00:51:43,726 --> 00:51:45,353
Come on. Arrest me. [Grunts]

701
00:51:45,436 --> 00:51:46,854
Just arrest me.

702
00:51:48,397 --> 00:51:49,398
Wait a minute.

703
00:51:50,107 --> 00:51:51,526
That a photo of your daughter?

704
00:51:53,444 --> 00:51:55,071
-Yeah
-Oh, so you're married?

705
00:51:55,696 --> 00:51:56,697
Yeah.

706
00:51:57,323 --> 00:51:59,075
You're married but you're here just…

707
00:51:59,158 --> 00:52:02,745
You're here messing around
with another woman? [Cries]

708
00:52:02,829 --> 00:52:04,890
- You're being unfaithful!
- I feel like he's about to lose it.

709
00:52:04,914 --> 00:52:07,458
- This is bad.
- Excuse me. I can help with that.

710
00:52:08,042 --> 00:52:09,252
[grunts]

711
00:52:10,378 --> 00:52:14,423
These are the records for the cargo trucks
Mr. Oh manages personally.

712
00:52:15,716 --> 00:52:17,927
[Man-sik] There are
about 15 illegal trucks in total.

713
00:52:18,427 --> 00:52:21,889
Uh… They transported the Candy
in seven trucks.

714
00:52:21,973 --> 00:52:23,558
These ones here.

715
00:52:23,641 --> 00:52:27,061
[sighs] I wonder where the hell
would Oh Jong-go be hiding?

716
00:52:27,144 --> 00:52:28,824
Min Ju-yeong is never
letting the Candy go.

717
00:52:28,855 --> 00:52:30,940
Okay. So if we follow the drug,

718
00:52:31,023 --> 00:52:32,984
we will eventually get to both of them.

719
00:52:33,526 --> 00:52:36,529
CCTV footage should help us
track down the trucks one by one.

720
00:52:36,612 --> 00:52:39,866
All right. I guess now it's back
to legwork, huh?

721
00:52:39,949 --> 00:52:41,509
[Jong-hyeon] I'll take a photo of this.

722
00:52:41,534 --> 00:52:42,869
- [Man-sik] Okay.
- [shutter clicks]

723
00:52:43,870 --> 00:52:45,079
All right.

724
00:52:45,162 --> 00:52:46,998
Let's split into two teams.

725
00:52:47,081 --> 00:52:49,625
And you, you're gonna stay
right where you are.

726
00:52:49,709 --> 00:52:50,710
What? Why?

727
00:52:50,793 --> 00:52:53,880
Why? You gotta be kidding me?
You know you're a wanted man, right?

728
00:52:53,963 --> 00:52:56,149
If someone spots you
and things go south, we're screwed.

729
00:52:56,173 --> 00:52:57,258
[sighs] Come on.

730
00:52:57,758 --> 00:53:03,431
Yeah, sure. Obviously it's hard to go
unnoticed with a pretty face like mine.

731
00:53:04,098 --> 00:53:05,641
But why can't I be incognito?

732
00:53:05,725 --> 00:53:07,268
That's impossible and you know it.

733
00:53:07,351 --> 00:53:09,329
You're gonna stay here, punk.
And just keep me posted.

734
00:53:09,353 --> 00:53:11,513
- Keep you posted. Come on.
- [Jong-hyeon] I'll take him.

735
00:53:12,565 --> 00:53:14,365
It's riskier for us
to leave him alone anyway.

736
00:53:14,400 --> 00:53:15,902
- [Man-sik] You sure?
- [scoffs]

737
00:53:15,985 --> 00:53:17,320
[Man-sik] You got a point.

738
00:53:17,403 --> 00:53:19,155
All right, take him with you.

739
00:53:19,238 --> 00:53:22,408
If he does screw up,
better if you're there when it happens.

740
00:53:22,491 --> 00:53:24,285
What do you think I am, huh? A child?

741
00:53:24,368 --> 00:53:27,204
You're worse than a child, idiot!
You're a goddamn fugitive.

742
00:53:27,288 --> 00:53:29,040
Quit whining and go, or stay put.

743
00:53:29,123 --> 00:53:30,499
Yeah, man. Come on.

744
00:53:34,295 --> 00:53:35,296
[Man-sik] Whoa, hang on.

745
00:53:35,379 --> 00:53:37,757
Kim, I just realized
you're not wearing your glasses.

746
00:53:38,341 --> 00:53:41,093
I mean, you look a lot better
without them. Almost as good as me.

747
00:53:41,177 --> 00:53:43,095
[Jae-Hong] You're right.
He does look better.

748
00:53:44,013 --> 00:53:46,491
What are you talking about?
It's the same dumb face. Well, come on.

749
00:53:46,515 --> 00:53:47,659
[Gwang-se] You're both good-looking!

750
00:53:47,683 --> 00:53:51,520
[yelps] Why are you doing this, huh?
[screaming]

751
00:53:54,148 --> 00:53:56,108
- [high-pitched ringing]
- [person groans]

752
00:53:56,192 --> 00:53:58,611
- I bought the plate from him too.
- [ringing fades]

753
00:53:58,694 --> 00:54:00,404
I've never even met Oh Jong-go!

754
00:54:00,488 --> 00:54:02,365
Well, if you've never met him,
why did you run?

755
00:54:02,448 --> 00:54:04,408
- I ran 'cause you told me you were cops!
- [sighs]

756
00:54:05,034 --> 00:54:06,702
[Jong-hyeon] Let me see the plate.

757
00:54:07,620 --> 00:54:09,747
I was scammed into buying it
a few days ago.

758
00:54:10,247 --> 00:54:11,540
I'm the victim here, all right?

759
00:54:12,416 --> 00:54:13,769
- Here it is.
- [Jong-hyeon] All right.

760
00:54:13,793 --> 00:54:14,961
Thanks for cooperating.

761
00:54:15,753 --> 00:54:16,837
- Geez.
- [sighs]

762
00:54:19,924 --> 00:54:20,925
What did he say?

763
00:54:21,634 --> 00:54:24,095
A few days ago he said
he was scammed into buying the plate.

764
00:54:25,763 --> 00:54:26,764
[sighs]

765
00:54:27,348 --> 00:54:29,058
If you feel tired, you should rest.

766
00:54:29,141 --> 00:54:30,601
I'll check out the rest on my own.

767
00:54:31,227 --> 00:54:33,020
Tired? What are you talking about?

768
00:54:33,104 --> 00:54:35,147
I'm made of steel, unlike someone I know.

769
00:54:36,774 --> 00:54:39,902
Just stay here, okay? You'll just
get in the way so take it easy.

770
00:54:41,862 --> 00:54:43,155
I see.

771
00:54:43,239 --> 00:54:46,826
Look, if you hate to be around me so much,
why'd you decide to bring me?

772
00:54:48,786 --> 00:54:50,037
'Cause it annoyed me.

773
00:54:50,538 --> 00:54:51,539
What?

774
00:54:53,958 --> 00:54:55,209
Han-na and I hanging out?

775
00:54:56,669 --> 00:54:57,837
Yeah.

776
00:55:00,840 --> 00:55:02,133
[sighs]

777
00:55:02,216 --> 00:55:03,342
[Dong-ju scoffs]

778
00:55:04,885 --> 00:55:06,012
Geez.

779
00:55:06,095 --> 00:55:08,848
Just started to like the guy,
and he ruins it.

780
00:55:09,515 --> 00:55:10,516
[sighs]

781
00:55:12,101 --> 00:55:13,644
[Dong-ju retches, vomits]

782
00:55:14,311 --> 00:55:15,688
[coughs, gags]

783
00:55:24,196 --> 00:55:25,197
[sighs]

784
00:55:26,157 --> 00:55:27,283
[phone buzzes]

785
00:55:29,035 --> 00:55:30,036
Chief, what's up?

786
00:55:31,037 --> 00:55:32,038
INSUNG JEIL ELECTRONICS

787
00:55:32,121 --> 00:55:34,933
[forensics chief] There are too many eyes
at the agency, so I did it here.

788
00:55:34,957 --> 00:55:36,876
It's my brother's shop so don't worry.

789
00:55:37,793 --> 00:55:38,794
All right.

790
00:55:43,090 --> 00:55:44,925
- [Han-na] Hello, sir.
- [chuckles]

791
00:55:45,009 --> 00:55:46,719
Well, the phone was pretty busted

792
00:55:46,802 --> 00:55:49,096
but I was able to recover
half of what was on there.

793
00:55:49,180 --> 00:55:50,264
That's wonderful.

794
00:55:54,393 --> 00:55:56,233
[Man-sik] What's the number
from the last call?

795
00:55:57,021 --> 00:55:59,899
Hmm? Four, seven, two, three? That's, um…

796
00:56:01,108 --> 00:56:02,735
Just hold on. Uh…

797
00:56:02,818 --> 00:56:04,487
Wait, do you know that number?

798
00:56:09,700 --> 00:56:10,910
LEE JONG-HUN

799
00:56:10,993 --> 00:56:12,161
[line ringing]

800
00:56:14,497 --> 00:56:16,123
[Man-sik] Wait, Lee Jong-hun?

801
00:56:16,707 --> 00:56:18,709
Who's that? Sounds familiar.

802
00:56:21,128 --> 00:56:22,588
The rookie over at RIU.

803
00:56:27,343 --> 00:56:29,804
Wait a minute.
It's starting to make sense.

804
00:56:30,513 --> 00:56:32,014
When Dong-ju was taken,

805
00:56:32,098 --> 00:56:34,183
RIU were the only ones
I forwarded the location to.

806
00:56:34,266 --> 00:56:36,560
Oh Jong-go just showing up
there was strange.

807
00:56:36,644 --> 00:56:39,730
Do you think Drug Demon taking his gun
was part of it all?

808
00:56:39,814 --> 00:56:41,273
That is was intentional.

809
00:56:41,357 --> 00:56:43,776
Who knows?
Could have been arranged like that.

810
00:56:43,859 --> 00:56:45,861
What we do know is this guy's our mole.

811
00:56:45,945 --> 00:56:47,947
Now it's all starting to make sense.

812
00:56:48,614 --> 00:56:49,657
Yeah, of course.

813
00:56:50,699 --> 00:56:53,202
When Drug Demon escaped,
he was the one watching her.

814
00:56:53,285 --> 00:56:56,705
I went to the bathroom for a second,
and when I got back, she was gone.

815
00:57:00,501 --> 00:57:01,710
[sighs] Jesus.

816
00:57:02,711 --> 00:57:04,213
- [Man-sik] Hey, Dae-yong.
- Yeah?

817
00:57:04,296 --> 00:57:06,715
- You with the rookie right now?
- You mean Jong-hun?

818
00:57:06,799 --> 00:57:09,969
He's on disciplinary leave
for losing his firearm to Drug Demon.

819
00:57:10,052 --> 00:57:11,679
Why? What's up?

820
00:57:14,014 --> 00:57:16,392
[Man-sik] All right.
We finally found the mole.

821
00:57:16,475 --> 00:57:18,435
Now all that's left
is to catch Min Ju-yeong.

822
00:57:18,519 --> 00:57:19,520
[police sirens wailing]

823
00:57:19,603 --> 00:57:22,481
Damn, look at that. What a spectacle.

824
00:57:23,315 --> 00:57:27,236
Over 500 officers have been dispatched
ordered by the commissioner himself.

825
00:57:27,820 --> 00:57:30,656
I heard through the grapevine
that he's sleeping at the agency.

826
00:57:31,824 --> 00:57:34,201
[Man-sik] Hell of a thing,
switching sides like that.

827
00:57:34,285 --> 00:57:35,995
Yeah, changed his tune pretty fast.

828
00:57:36,579 --> 00:57:38,455
The man is nervous.
The tables have turned.

829
00:57:38,539 --> 00:57:40,666
Now where's that bastard
Min Ju-yeong hiding?

830
00:57:40,749 --> 00:57:43,669
All these people tearing the city apart
and not even a glimpse of him?

831
00:57:43,752 --> 00:57:44,962
Son of a bitch.

832
00:57:54,597 --> 00:57:55,681
[phone buzzing]

833
00:57:56,974 --> 00:57:58,642
Hey, Dae-yong. Where's your rookie?

834
00:58:03,564 --> 00:58:07,067
[tense music playing]

835
00:58:07,151 --> 00:58:09,445
[sirens wailing]

836
00:58:12,156 --> 00:58:14,950
[officer crying] No, it can't be.

837
00:58:15,034 --> 00:58:17,036
- Hey.
- [officer] What the hell is this, man?

838
00:58:17,119 --> 00:58:18,597
- What the hell happened to him?
- [officer crying]

839
00:58:18,621 --> 00:58:19,830
[Dae-yong] I don't know.

840
00:58:19,914 --> 00:58:21,749
We were called out here too.

841
00:58:21,832 --> 00:58:25,127
Jong-hun is not that kind of man.
Something's off here.

842
00:58:25,211 --> 00:58:28,464
- [officer crying] Oh, God.
- [officer 2] Jong-hun!

843
00:58:43,103 --> 00:58:45,105
Min Ju-yeong couldn't have
escaped so easily

844
00:58:45,648 --> 00:58:47,900
and make it
out of Goldengate Central unseen.

845
00:58:48,400 --> 00:58:51,070
[sighs] All of the firefighters
and officers.

846
00:58:51,779 --> 00:58:52,780
God.

847
00:58:53,364 --> 00:58:55,115
How in the world did he get out?

848
00:59:01,538 --> 00:59:03,874
[Jong-hyeon] Over 500 officers
have been dispatched

849
00:59:03,958 --> 00:59:05,751
ordered by the commissioner himself.

850
00:59:05,834 --> 00:59:07,628
Hell of a thing,
switching sides like that.

851
00:59:08,420 --> 00:59:11,090
I heard through the grapevine
that he's sleeping at the agency.

852
00:59:15,094 --> 00:59:16,762
[Dong-ju] You goddamn coward.

853
00:59:19,598 --> 00:59:22,559
Min Ju-yeong, I think I know where he is.

854
00:59:24,270 --> 00:59:27,106
Guys like him when they sense danger,

855
00:59:27,189 --> 00:59:30,234
they scurry off and hide
in the safest place they can find.

856
00:59:31,277 --> 00:59:33,779
Right next to the biggest guy in the room.

857
00:59:36,657 --> 00:59:38,033
Did you speak to the mayor yet?

858
00:59:38,659 --> 00:59:39,660
[Pan-yeol] Ah, yes.

859
00:59:39,743 --> 00:59:43,080
He said he will…
He'll have someone come over soon.

860
00:59:46,583 --> 00:59:48,752
Can I offer you some tea perhaps?

861
00:59:48,836 --> 00:59:50,629
I have quality green tea.

862
00:59:52,798 --> 00:59:54,008
[tires screech]

863
00:59:57,594 --> 00:59:59,596
SAFE INSUNG, HAPPY CITIZENS

864
00:59:59,680 --> 01:00:01,000
INSUNG METROPOLITAN POLICE AGENCY

865
01:00:06,854 --> 01:00:07,855
I can't let you pass.

866
01:00:09,023 --> 01:00:10,024
I'm going up.

867
01:00:12,067 --> 01:00:13,569
Please. Oh, my God.

868
01:00:13,652 --> 01:00:14,653
Get off me.

869
01:00:15,154 --> 01:00:16,572
Move. I'm going. You can't stop me.

870
01:00:16,655 --> 01:00:18,341
- What are you doing?
- [officer] Don't let him pass.

871
01:00:18,365 --> 01:00:20,093
- He can't get through.
- Come on now. Get the hell off me.

872
01:00:20,117 --> 01:00:23,078
Come on. Come on.
Why the hell are you trying to stop me?

873
01:00:23,162 --> 01:00:24,663
[captain] Who the hell are you?

874
01:00:24,747 --> 01:00:26,165
Nobody else gets upstairs.

875
01:00:26,248 --> 01:00:27,624
Nobody? Shut up.

876
01:00:27,708 --> 01:00:29,508
Come on. What are you assholes
trying to hide?

877
01:00:33,005 --> 01:00:34,173
Okay, what's going on here?

878
01:00:34,256 --> 01:00:36,026
- Stop. Stop. Let me pass.
- [officers clamoring]

879
01:00:36,050 --> 01:00:38,761
- Tell me whose orders you're acting on.
- [officer 2] Get back.

880
01:00:38,844 --> 01:00:41,430
Step aside or you'll be held
legally accountable.

881
01:00:41,513 --> 01:00:44,058
What? You guys are trying to stop us
from going up there?

882
01:00:44,141 --> 01:00:45,225
Let me past. Step aside.

883
01:00:45,309 --> 01:00:46,852
- [exclaims]
- Don't touch them.

884
01:00:46,935 --> 01:00:48,520
- Throw your hands up!
- Don't touch me!

885
01:00:48,604 --> 01:00:49,813
[all clamoring]

886
01:00:50,481 --> 01:00:51,482
[Jong-hyeon] Let me pass.

887
01:00:51,565 --> 01:00:53,233
Come on. Get your hands off me.

888
01:00:59,948 --> 01:01:01,450
Oh, hey. [Scoffs]

889
01:01:01,533 --> 01:01:04,370
So that's where you've been hiding,
you spineless son of a bitch.

890
01:01:04,453 --> 01:01:06,372
[captain] Sir, what's going on?

891
01:01:07,498 --> 01:01:08,665
[gasps]

892
01:01:09,249 --> 01:01:10,751
Down with the guns! Put them down.

893
01:01:10,834 --> 01:01:13,796
Hey, Min Ju-yeong. Hey, hey.
Put the gun down.

894
01:01:15,381 --> 01:01:16,465
[Pan-yeol groans]

895
01:01:17,466 --> 01:01:21,136
Hey, hey, hey. Stand down. Stand down.
He's going. He's gonna go now.

896
01:01:21,220 --> 01:01:22,221
Down with the guns.

897
01:01:22,805 --> 01:01:25,182
Oh, shit. Goddamn it.

898
01:01:32,981 --> 01:01:34,775
- [gasping]
- [yelps]

899
01:01:35,442 --> 01:01:36,693
Hey, Ji Han-na!

900
01:01:37,403 --> 01:01:39,279
Put down the gun. Put it down!

901
01:01:39,363 --> 01:01:42,616
Ji Han-na, now put down the gun.
This second!

902
01:01:42,699 --> 01:01:44,660
Listen, you're gambling with my life here.

903
01:01:45,702 --> 01:01:47,371
- [gunshot]
- [groans]

904
01:01:50,999 --> 01:01:52,084
- [gunshot]
- [groans]

905
01:01:55,712 --> 01:01:59,466
[screaming]

906
01:02:00,092 --> 01:02:01,093
[captain] Commissioner!

907
01:02:02,719 --> 01:02:05,514
- Commissioner!
- [Pan-yeol screaming]

908
01:02:05,597 --> 01:02:07,492
Did you hear that?
That was a gunshot. Did you hear it?

909
01:02:07,516 --> 01:02:08,636
All of us together. Come on.

910
01:02:08,684 --> 01:02:10,769
Guys, one, two, three. Let's go!

911
01:02:10,853 --> 01:02:12,688
- [grunts]
- [shouts]

912
01:02:16,191 --> 01:02:18,169
- [officer] Don't move. Don't move.
- [Pan-yeol groans]

913
01:02:18,193 --> 01:02:20,279
- [screams]
- [officers clamoring]

914
01:02:20,362 --> 01:02:23,198
[Pan-yeol] Hey, hey!
Don't touch it! Don't touch it!

915
01:02:23,282 --> 01:02:25,701
[groans]

916
01:02:27,619 --> 01:02:28,704
Kim, where you going?

917
01:02:30,414 --> 01:02:32,124
[officers clamoring]

918
01:02:32,207 --> 01:02:35,252
[Pan-yeol] Ow. Ow. Hey, hey,
be careful, you idiots!

919
01:02:36,920 --> 01:02:39,548
Officer Ji Han-na shot at him, sir.

920
01:02:39,631 --> 01:02:41,508
Come on. Now, idiot, let's go.

921
01:02:41,592 --> 01:02:43,343
Damn it. Stop bouncing up and down.

922
01:02:43,427 --> 01:02:45,512
[officers exclaiming]

923
01:02:45,596 --> 01:02:47,681
- [Pan-yeol] Hurry up, idiots!
- She shot him?

924
01:02:47,764 --> 01:02:48,765
Seems like it.

925
01:02:48,849 --> 01:02:49,850
Shit happens.

926
01:02:49,933 --> 01:02:52,060
Yeah, well, I mean, what are you gonna do?

927
01:02:53,145 --> 01:02:54,188
All right then.

928
01:02:56,899 --> 01:02:57,900
[phone beeps]

929
01:03:01,862 --> 01:03:03,864
Hey, going somewhere?

930
01:03:03,947 --> 01:03:04,990
[groans]

931
01:03:08,327 --> 01:03:09,786
Hope you have insurance.

932
01:03:09,870 --> 01:03:11,246
[grunts] Shit.

933
01:03:11,330 --> 01:03:13,540
If you don't,
I can hook you up with a guy.

934
01:03:14,124 --> 01:03:17,252
'Cause I'm gonna break
every last bone in your body.

935
01:03:19,046 --> 01:03:22,341
[groaning]

936
01:03:29,056 --> 01:03:32,309
I thought I left you beaten,
but you're hard to put down.

937
01:03:32,392 --> 01:03:34,269
You shouldn't have underestimated me.

938
01:03:35,145 --> 01:03:36,271
Now shut up, you thug.

939
01:03:36,355 --> 01:03:37,523
[sighs]

940
01:03:39,316 --> 01:03:41,902
[Ju-yeong] No,
I think you underestimated me, kid.

941
01:03:41,985 --> 01:03:44,238
- [grunts]
- [groans]

942
01:03:47,032 --> 01:03:48,742
[car tires squealing]

943
01:03:58,001 --> 01:03:59,753
[car tires squealing]

944
01:04:15,269 --> 01:04:16,562
[car horn honks]

945
01:04:17,187 --> 01:04:18,272
Dong-ju, hey!

946
01:04:26,321 --> 01:04:27,781
[groans]

947
01:04:31,285 --> 01:04:33,662
[Jong-go] Hey, where you going?

948
01:04:37,833 --> 01:04:38,959
[chuckles]

949
01:04:41,336 --> 01:04:42,879
Ah, shit.

950
01:04:44,464 --> 01:04:46,842
Look who decided to show up in the end.

951
01:04:46,925 --> 01:04:47,968
Thought you ran away.

952
01:04:48,051 --> 01:04:51,221
What? Why would I run? You're right here.

953
01:04:51,305 --> 01:04:52,931
[laughs]

954
01:04:57,394 --> 01:04:58,645
[groans]

955
01:05:01,315 --> 01:05:02,649
[Jong-go] Geez.

956
01:05:03,734 --> 01:05:05,652
Give it a rest, kid.

957
01:05:06,737 --> 01:05:10,574
I'm getting sick of this shit.
Ah, for God's sake. [Clicks tongue]

958
01:05:14,995 --> 01:05:16,204
Seriously?

959
01:05:18,999 --> 01:05:21,793
[breathing heavily]

960
01:05:28,425 --> 01:05:29,760
[Jong-go] Ah.

961
01:05:31,386 --> 01:05:32,554
Geez. This guy.

962
01:05:39,269 --> 01:05:40,270
[echoing] What?

963
01:05:41,188 --> 01:05:43,106
Don't tell me you can't see.

964
01:05:43,190 --> 01:05:44,470
What are you talking about, huh?

965
01:05:56,161 --> 01:05:57,162
[Jong-go] Hey.

966
01:06:02,709 --> 01:06:03,710
[sighs]

967
01:06:04,628 --> 01:06:05,921
What a tragedy.

968
01:06:07,506 --> 01:06:09,424
You're really losing your vision.

969
01:06:11,134 --> 01:06:14,096
Told you to keep that blood pressure
in check, didn't I?

970
01:06:15,931 --> 01:06:19,059
You know, when your coach
tells you something, you should listen.

971
01:06:20,310 --> 01:06:23,146
How in the hell
are you gonna take me on like this?

972
01:06:26,316 --> 01:06:27,317
[groans]

973
01:06:28,694 --> 01:06:29,695
[clatters]

974
01:06:41,039 --> 01:06:42,416
[hisses]

975
01:06:45,377 --> 01:06:47,129
[gentle music playing]

976
01:06:58,640 --> 01:07:01,810
♪ Stand up and dry your eyes  ♪

977
01:07:17,451 --> 01:07:18,744
[Han-na] Jong-hyeon!

978
01:07:19,578 --> 01:07:20,620
Yoon Dong-ju!

979
01:07:22,497 --> 01:07:23,749
[Man-sik] Hold on!

980
01:07:23,832 --> 01:07:25,375
[groans]

981
01:07:25,459 --> 01:07:28,646
Listen, Commissioner, this is the biggest
mess. You can't just watch it play out.

982
01:07:28,670 --> 01:07:30,148
[Dae-yong] I don't think that
Jong-hun was one of them.

983
01:07:30,172 --> 01:07:31,798
So there's another mole then.

984
01:07:31,882 --> 01:07:33,482
[Dae-yong] That damn mole is on my team.

985
01:07:34,050 --> 01:07:35,427
I don't know how to step in.

986
01:07:36,303 --> 01:07:38,138
[Man-sik] Money isn't the
only thing he has?

987
01:07:38,221 --> 01:07:39,556
If it's not money then…

988
01:07:39,639 --> 01:07:41,641
There's only one guy we have to ask.

989
01:07:41,725 --> 01:07:44,144
He's gonna make the first move.

990
01:07:44,227 --> 01:07:47,689
[Man-sik] Min Ju-yeong's going to
Gumyeon-dong through Gumyeon Intersection.

991
01:07:48,356 --> 01:07:50,650
[Dong-ju] I really mean that much to you?

992
01:07:50,734 --> 01:07:53,111
[Han-na] How long were you planning
to pretend you're fine?

993
01:07:53,195 --> 01:07:54,338
[Ju-yeong] Look forward to it.

994
01:07:54,362 --> 01:07:56,072
[Dong-ju] Han-na, are you on your way?

995
01:07:56,156 --> 01:07:58,867
[Ju-yeong] Today is going to be
a day to remember.
